39namespace webrtc {
40
41class RtpPacketSinkInterface;
42class VideoDecoderFactory;
43
44class VideoReceiveStream {
45 public:
46 // Class for handling moving in/out recording state.
47 struct RecordingState {
48 RecordingState() = default;
49 explicit RecordingState(
50 std::function<void(const RecordableEncodedFrame&)> callback)
51 : callback(std::move(callback)) {}
52
53 // Callback stored from the VideoReceiveStream. The VideoReceiveStream
54 // client should not interpret the attribute.
55 std::function<void(const RecordableEncodedFrame&)> callback;
56 // Memento of internal state in VideoReceiveStream, recording wether
57 // we're currently causing generation of a keyframe from the sender. Needed
58 // to avoid sending double keyframe requests. The VideoReceiveStream client
59 // should not interpret the attribute.
60 bool keyframe_needed = false;
61 // Memento of when a keyframe request was last sent. The VideoReceiveStream
62 // client should not interpret the attribute.
63 absl::optional<int64_t> last_keyframe_request_ms;
64 };
65
66 // TODO(mflodman) Move all these settings to VideoDecoder and move the
67 // declaration to common_types.h.
68 struct Decoder {
69 Decoder();
70 Decoder(const Decoder&);
71 ~Decoder();
72 std::string ToString() const;
73
74 SdpVideoFormat video_format;
75
76 // Received RTP packets with this payload type will be sent to this decoder
77 // instance.
78 int payload_type = 0;
79 };
80
81 struct Stats {
82 Stats();
83 ~Stats();
84 std::string ToString(int64_t time_ms) const;
85
86 int network_frame_rate = 0;
87 int decode_frame_rate = 0;
88 int render_frame_rate = 0;
89 uint32_t frames_rendered = 0;
90
91 // Decoder stats.
92 std::string decoder_implementation_name = "unknown";
93 FrameCounts frame_counts;
94 int decode_ms = 0;
95 int max_decode_ms = 0;
96 int current_delay_ms = 0;
97 int target_delay_ms = 0;
98 int jitter_buffer_ms = 0;
99 // https://w3c.github.io/webrtc-stats/#dom-rtcvideoreceiverstats-jitterbufferdelay
100 double jitter_buffer_delay_seconds = 0;
101 // https://w3c.github.io/webrtc-stats/#dom-rtcvideoreceiverstats-jitterbufferemittedcount
102 uint64_t jitter_buffer_emitted_count = 0;
103 int min_playout_delay_ms = 0;
104 int render_delay_ms = 10;
105 int64_t interframe_delay_max_ms = -1;
106 // Frames dropped due to decoding failures or if the system is too slow.
107 // https://www.w3.org/TR/webrtc-stats/#dom-rtcvideoreceiverstats-framesdropped
108 uint32_t frames_dropped = 0;
109 uint32_t frames_decoded = 0;
110 // https://w3c.github.io/webrtc-stats/#dom-rtcinboundrtpstreamstats-totaldecodetime
111 uint64_t total_decode_time_ms = 0;
112 // Total inter frame delay in seconds.
113 // https://w3c.github.io/webrtc-stats/#dom-rtcinboundrtpstreamstats-totalinterframedelay
114 double total_inter_frame_delay = 0;
115 // Total squared inter frame delay in seconds^2.
116 // https://w3c.github.io/webrtc-stats/#dom-rtcinboundrtpstreamstats-totalsqauredinterframedelay
117 double total_squared_inter_frame_delay = 0;
118 int64_t first_frame_received_to_decoded_ms = -1;
119 absl::optional<uint64_t> qp_sum;
120
121 int current_payload_type = -1;
122
123 int total_bitrate_bps = 0;
124
125 int width = 0;
126 int height = 0;
127
128 uint32_t freeze_count = 0;
129 uint32_t pause_count = 0;
130 uint32_t total_freezes_duration_ms = 0;
131 uint32_t total_pauses_duration_ms = 0;
132 uint32_t total_frames_duration_ms = 0;
133 double sum_squared_frame_durations = 0.0;
134
135 VideoContentType content_type = VideoContentType::UNSPECIFIED;
136
137 // https://w3c.github.io/webrtc-stats/#dom-rtcinboundrtpstreamstats-estimatedplayouttimestamp
138 absl::optional<int64_t> estimated_playout_ntp_timestamp_ms;
139 int sync_offset_ms = std::numeric_limits<int>::max();
140
141 uint32_t ssrc = 0;
142 std::string c_name;
143 RtpReceiveStats rtp_stats;
144 RtcpPacketTypeCounter rtcp_packet_type_counts;
145
146 // Timing frame info: all important timestamps for a full lifetime of a
147 // single 'timing frame'.
148 absl::optional<webrtc::TimingFrameInfo> timing_frame_info;
149 };
150
151 struct Config {
152 private:
153 // Access to the copy constructor is private to force use of the Copy()
154 // method for those exceptional cases where we do use it.
155 Config(const Config&);
156
157 public:
158 Config() = delete;
159 Config(Config&&);
160 explicit Config(Transport* rtcp_send_transport);
161 Config& operator=(Config&&);
162 Config& operator=(const Config&) = delete;
163 ~Config();
164
165 // Mostly used by tests. Avoid creating copies if you can.
166 Config Copy() const { return Config(*this); }
167
168 std::string ToString() const;
169
170 // Decoders for every payload that we can receive.
171 std::vector<Decoder> decoders;
172
173 // Ownership stays with WebrtcVideoEngine (delegated from PeerConnection).
174 VideoDecoderFactory* decoder_factory = nullptr;
175
176 // Receive-stream specific RTP settings.
177 struct Rtp {
178 Rtp();
179 Rtp(const Rtp&);
180 ~Rtp();
181 std::string ToString() const;
182
183 // Synchronization source (stream identifier) to be received.
184 uint32_t remote_ssrc = 0;
185
186 // Sender SSRC used for sending RTCP (such as receiver reports).
187 uint32_t local_ssrc = 0;
188
189 // See RtcpMode for description.
190 RtcpMode rtcp_mode = RtcpMode::kCompound;
191
192 // Extended RTCP settings.
193 struct RtcpXr {
194 // True if RTCP Receiver Reference Time Report Block extension
195 // (RFC 3611) should be enabled.
196 bool receiver_reference_time_report = false;
197 } rtcp_xr;
198
199 // See draft-holmer-rmcat-transport-wide-cc-extensions for details.
200 bool transport_cc = false;
201
202 // See LntfConfig for description.
203 LntfConfig lntf;
204
205 // See NackConfig for description.
206 NackConfig nack;
207
208 // Payload types for ULPFEC and RED, respectively.
209 int ulpfec_payload_type = -1;
210 int red_payload_type = -1;
211
212 // SSRC for retransmissions.
213 uint32_t rtx_ssrc = 0;
214
215 // Set if the stream is protected using FlexFEC.
216 bool protected_by_flexfec = false;
217
218 // Optional callback sink to support additional packet handlsers such as
219 // FlexFec.
220 RtpPacketSinkInterface* packet_sink_ = nullptr;
221
222 // Map from rtx payload type -> media payload type.
223 // For RTX to be enabled, both an SSRC and this mapping are needed.
224 std::map<int, int> rtx_associated_payload_types;
225
226 // Payload types that should be depacketized using raw depacketizer
227 // (payload header will not be parsed and must not be present, additional
228 // meta data is expected to be present in generic frame descriptor
229 // RTP header extension).
230 std::set<int> raw_payload_types;
231
232 // RTP header extensions used for the received stream.
233 std::vector<RtpExtension> extensions;
234 } rtp;
235
236 // Transport for outgoing packets (RTCP).
237 Transport* rtcp_send_transport = nullptr;
238
239 // Must always be set.
240 rtc::VideoSinkInterface<VideoFrame>* renderer = nullptr;
241
242 // Expected delay needed by the renderer, i.e. the frame will be delivered
243 // this many milliseconds, if possible, earlier than the ideal render time.
244 int render_delay_ms = 10;
245
246 // If false, pass frames on to the renderer as soon as they are
247 // available.
248 bool enable_prerenderer_smoothing = true;
249
250 // Identifier for an A/V synchronization group. Empty string to disable.
251 // TODO(pbos): Synchronize streams in a sync group, not just video streams
252 // to one of the audio streams.
253 std::string sync_group;
254
255 // Target delay in milliseconds. A positive value indicates this stream is
256 // used for streaming instead of a real-time call.
257 int target_delay_ms = 0;
258
259 // An optional custom frame decryptor that allows the entire frame to be
260 // decrypted in whatever way the caller choses. This is not required by
261 // default.
262 rtc::scoped_refptr<webrtc::FrameDecryptorInterface> frame_decryptor;
263
264 // Per PeerConnection cryptography options.
265 CryptoOptions crypto_options;
266
267 rtc::scoped_refptr<webrtc::FrameTransformerInterface> frame_transformer;
268 };
269
270 // Starts stream activity.
271 // When a stream is active, it can receive, process and deliver packets.
272 virtual void Start() = 0;
273 // Stops stream activity.
274 // When a stream is stopped, it can't receive, process or deliver packets.
275 virtual void Stop() = 0;
276
277 // TODO(pbos): Add info on currently-received codec to Stats.
278 virtual Stats GetStats() const = 0;
279
280 virtual std::vector<RtpSource> GetSources() const = 0;
281
282 // Sets a base minimum for the playout delay. Base minimum delay sets lower
283 // bound on minimum delay value determining lower bound on playout delay.
284 //
285 // Returns true if value was successfully set, false overwise.
286 virtual bool SetBaseMinimumPlayoutDelayMs(int delay_ms) = 0;
287
288 // Returns current value of base minimum delay in milliseconds.
289 virtual int GetBaseMinimumPlayoutDelayMs() const = 0;
290
291 // Allows a FrameDecryptor to be attached to a VideoReceiveStream after
292 // creation without resetting the decoder state.
293 virtual void SetFrameDecryptor(
294 rtc::scoped_refptr<FrameDecryptorInterface> frame_decryptor) = 0;
295
296 // Allows a frame transformer to be attached to a VideoReceiveStream after
297 // creation without resetting the decoder state.
298 virtual void SetDepacketizerToDecoderFrameTransformer(
299 rtc::scoped_refptr<FrameTransformerInterface> frame_transformer) = 0;
300
301 // Sets and returns recording state. The old state is moved out
302 // of the video receive stream and returned to the caller, and |state|
303 // is moved in. If the state's callback is set, it will be called with
304 // recordable encoded frames as they arrive.
305 // If |generate_key_frame| is true, the method will generate a key frame.
306 // When the function returns, it's guaranteed that all old callouts
307 // to the returned callback has ceased.
308 // Note: the client should not interpret the returned state's attributes, but
309 // instead treat it as opaque data.
310 virtual RecordingState SetAndGetRecordingState(RecordingState state,
311 bool generate_key_frame) = 0;
312
313 // Cause eventual generation of a key frame from the sender.
314 virtual void GenerateKeyFrame() = 0;
315
316 protected:
317 virtual ~VideoReceiveStream() {}
318};
319
320class DEPRECATED_VideoReceiveStream : public VideoReceiveStream {
321 public:
322 // RtpDemuxer only forwards a given RTP packet to one sink. However, some
323 // sinks, such as FlexFEC, might wish to be informed of all of the packets
324 // a given sink receives (or any set of sinks). They may do so by registering
325 // themselves as secondary sinks.
326 virtual void AddSecondarySink(RtpPacketSinkInterface* sink) = 0;
327 virtual void RemoveSecondarySink(const RtpPacketSinkInterface* sink) = 0;
328};
